For Inpainting Prompt:
GPT4-vision will be used to inject this content into the image (in place of the masked regions). If this prompt is empty, GPT will imagine what's there (guess mode).



For Masking Prompt:
- If the string is non-empty: the string will be used to auto-generate a mask using Florence2 + SAM
- If the string is empty, the provided mask image will be used instead. This means that EITHER a mask image OR a masking prompt must be provided!

Propose a visual description for this image. IMPORTANT: re-imagine the black (masked) regions in the image based on the provided inpainting prompt. If no inpainting prompt is given, just imagine what might naturally fit in those spaces. Limit the final imagined image description to 50 words. Dont mention the black regions, just reply with the full description of that new imagined image, nothing else. Inpainting prompt:

Give me a visual description of this image (IMPORTANT: ignore the black, missing regions completely in your description!!). Limit the description to max 50 words. Reply with just the description, nothing else.
Will only have an effect when masking_prompt = empty!
